        [],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You remember the night he came, it was like a blistering tempest in your face. The pores had long since bore sweat, but his wrath made your skin gloss and shine like stones in a river of your own blood. You could feel the cusp of his power, bridled as it was, pressing your memories out of your mind like a strainger. \"I'll hold these for you,\" Irritum hissed, and you watched stills of someone else's memories - someone else's Sire, brother, teachings, goodnight kisses of a mortal mother, and spars with mortal brothers, put into the demon's pocket. \"You'll want these instead, they'll suit you better.\" The demon said with a wink, extending your memories in his boil scarred hand, flashes of anger, resentment, a failed sire, anger. Your tongue swelled and your tarnish soul thirst for their blood. It thirsted for so much blood. ---- He visits you in your dreams, often by the river Styx, and every time you go the souls turn red and sproud cysts as he dips his pus covered feet into the current. \"Another demon's servant has left plague in your city.\" Irritum tells you, his bloodshot eyes only half see you. \"It has drawn both healers and other infernalists to your location, they threaten your existence there. Get rid of them, but let the illness grow, weed out the hunters. Do this, and you can have one back.\" Irritum's sickly hand reveals another man's memory, but in it is your own brother, a blood stained face dragging you from a fire so hot it burns you just looking at it."
        ],
        [
